SIMPLE: carpentry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carpentry
<hw>Car"pen*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>charpenterie</ets>, OF. also <ets>carpenterie</ets>. See
<er>Carpenter</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The art of cutting, framing, and joining timber, as
in the construction of buildings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An assemblage of pieces of timber connected by being
framed together, as the pieces of a roof, floor, etc.; work done by a
carpenter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carper</ent>⟦br⟧
